  <static seed="1259" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions80.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5}{y-2}-\frac{10y}{y^{2}-4}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{5}{y+2}, y\ne 2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5}{y-2}-\frac{10y}{y^{2}-4}} 
      \amp = {\frac{5}{y-2}}-\frac{10 y}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{5\cdot({y+2})}{({y-2})\cdot({y+2})} -\frac{10 y}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{5\mathopen{}\left(y+2\right)-10y}}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{5y+10-10y}}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-5y+10}}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-5\mathopen{}\left(y-2\right)}}{(y - 2)(y + 2)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{5}{y+2}, y\ne 2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{y-2}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne {2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
